page.title: 09Horningtoft Church
page.content: Horningtoft Church is called St Edmunds because the church was built in the times of Edward the third. It is mainly built of stone.The doors are built of wood and the floor is made of stone. The church has no tower because it fell down in 1796.It caused a lot of damage to the church,but everything was repaired and redecorated the next year. The organ is in the nave next to the vestery which is where the priest gets changed and where he gets things ready.The seats in the nave are not pews but fold up chairs.They are made of wood and there are 85 of them. The font is on the south side of the church and many people have been baptised in it.The pulpit is in the nave near the chancel on the north side. CONTINUED ON PAGE 10
